To establish a baseline profile of mental health status, participants completed the CES-D (Radloff, 1977; Lewinsohn et al., 1997) self-report measure at the in-person screening assessment to assess for depressive symptoms. Participants responded to each of the 20 items using a 4-point Likert scale (0 = rarely or none of the time and 3 = most or almost all of the time), in which higher total sum scores reflect more depressive symptoms. However, participants were deemed ineligible for the study if they received a score \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
